<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf67a6065-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7310"><num value="7310">§ 7310.</num><heading> Able seamen—offshore supply vessels</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For service on a vessel of less than 500 gross tons as measured under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14502">section 14502 of this title</ref>, or an alternate tonnage measured under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14302">section 14302 of this title</ref> as prescribed by the Secretary under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14104">section 14104 of this title</ref> engaged in support of exploration, exploitation, or production of offshore mineral or energy resources, an individual may be rated as able seaman—offshore supply vessels if the individual has at least 6 months’ service on deck on board vessels operating on the oceans or the navigable waters of the United States (including the Great Lakes).</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf67a6066-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/543">97 Stat. 543</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/104/324/tVII/s722">Pub. L. 104–324, title VII, § 722</ref>, <date date="1996-10-19">Oct. 19, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3938">110 Stat. 3938</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
